  <b>Bardtail</b> - Jul 10, 2004 - 08:32 AM<br />
  <b>Post subject: </b>A poor decision.....<hr width=95% class="sep"/>
  Who would have thought that after just a month in a guild I'd miss you guys so much?  But the fact is I do.  I made a poor decision by leaving PS, no doubt about it.  I miss the guild chatter and the friends I made.  It isn't quite the same grouping with Fude, Trask, and Deest without being able to hear the other side of the conversation.  <img src="./modules/PNphpBB2/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I've freed up some time in my schedule and actually got a few things done I wanted to finish.  Nearly done with my epic, camped my iksar mask, tiny cloak of darkest night.....and some other things.  I feel much less stressed about the time schedule raiding requires.  
<br />

<br />
I know I might have disrespected the guild tag of PS.  I'm very sorry.  I was proud to wear the Prime Syndicate under my name and would very much like to do so again.  I tend to be wordy sometimes so I'll wrap it up, but I apologize for my hasty decision to leave and would like to reapply to PS if you'll have me back.  Traskul buddy, got a room for a recruit again?  <img src="./modules/PNphpBB2/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
There will be a concern about me leaving again and I can assure you all that I will be there for the long hall.  I've seen both sides of raiding, gone back to normal playing and found I miss the raiding more than I thought I would, but especially the great people in Prime Syndicate!
<br />

<br />
Thanks for considering taking me back.  Sorry it is necessary.  <img src="./modules/PNphpBB2/images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="Sad" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Bardtail
