  <b>Deestroyr</b> - Jul 10, 2004 - 09:12 AM<br />
  <b>Post subject: </b><hr width=95% class="sep"/>
  glad to see you've given it some thought again bud.  What can I say.  The first time i grouped with Bardtail was during Agnarr raid when i forget what went wrong but people started dying and kelvas got summoned and pwned =*(.  Anyhow, i lost soe and as soon as that happened bardtail was there to selos my sorry ranger ass so i could resoe myself and kite agnarr.  Kiting is so much more fun with selos =D.  
<br />

<br />
IMO i think we could really use a bard who isnt a bot and can pull.  The only problem is hes not ep flagged yet but thats fine, when he is ill help him get to know fire and some of that good stuff myself, and who knows we could save some time on tough pulls with a bard helpin that can fade etc.  Before coming to PS, I had never seen monk-only pulling teams, but that works too.  But a bard or two in the pulling team wouldnt hurt either, if anything it would save us time from having to clear things that we wouldnt have to clear with a bard (ie all the magma giants).  With time saved, we could hit more targets, and get more gear in during a nite with full attendance etc.  I think a bard who is being played by only 1 person and is not a bot could come a long way to helping PS, despite his lack of experience wtih EP, he can definitely learn the stuff and help make a great contribution.  Those are just some of my thoughts ~ Deestroyr
